                           <note>
                           Written in a crude hand.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Madḫāne ʿĀlam is written on <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a human: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>.&#xD;
- Encompassed writing on <locus target="#37ra">37ra</locus>, 38rb.&#xD;
- Erasures: e.g., <locus target="#24va">24va</locus>, 63va.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: <locus target="#6rb">6rb</locus>, 23vb.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words are written interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#6rb">6rb</locus>, 13ra, 14va, 21vb, 35va.&#xD;
- Immediate corrections marked by thin lines above and below the words: <locus target="#14ra">14ra</locus>, 79va.&#xD;
- Lacunae (space for rubricated names left unfilled): e.g., <locus target="#48vb">48vb</locus>, 55vab, 56vab, 57rb, 58ra.&#xD;
- Pen trials: <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.&#xD;
- Scribbles and doodles: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 2r, 2v, 79v, 80r, 81r, 82r.</item>
                     </list>
